  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing resilience of people impacted by economic crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sri Lanka is undergoing a disastrous economic crisis due partly to COVID-19 but also to unmanageable levels of fiscal deficit and sovereign debt leading to default.  Food and fuel supplies, and medicines, are running out, and the agricultural system which was dependent on imported inputs has largely collapsed.  Many families have lost their means of earning income, and such food as is available has become unaffordable for many households.

SEDEC/ Caritas Sri Lanka will implement a multi-sectoral response to the emergency involving distribution of food rations, medical and psychosocial assistance, support to children&apos;s schooling, along with livelihood rehabilitation and measures to help people build their resilience and coping strategies.</narrative>
  </description>
